cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing tasks, specifically unsupervised similarity tasks. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of deep recurrent models, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The concept of an optimal representation space is a fundamental concept in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also introduces new sentence embedding models, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the models are based on visual features. Finally, the paper discusses the use of distributed representations for transfer tasks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
